datastructures.trees

Class AVLBinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.trees.LinkedBinarySearchTree<T>
      • datastructures.trees.AVLBinarySearchTree<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The Comparable Type held by the AVLBinarySearchTree container.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BinarySearchTree<T>, Tree<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class AVLBinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends LinkedBinarySearchTree<T>

    AVLBinarySearchTree is an implementation of an Adelskon - Velskii - Landis (AVL) BST. These trees use rotation operations to maintain the invariant that after every insertion or deletion, the siblings of the tree are at most one level apart of one another. Such trees therefore approximate logn height.

    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
